race.comment: DAMAS (3) just missed at Wangaratta before the break and will be better for his two runs this preparation. Was a touch flat last time off a narrow defeat first-up and he's on a 9-day return. Well placed to take this out. MISS LOTTIE (13) didn't have much luck at Tatura but missed a whisker at Wangaratta the one before. That effort would see her in the finish. DRY FIRE (5) didn't have much luck at Kyenton but went well at Wodonga prior. Has an inside barrier today and a key gear switch. OVER THE STARS (12) resumed in stronger at Terang and needed the outing. He's proven second up and good enough to play a leading role.
